      "role": "user",
      "content": "but \"finding joy in the present\" feels like such a cope. it's like saying a movie is good even though you know it's going to end and the theater is gonna be empty and dark. if the end result for everything is just nothingness, isn't all this effort just a way to distract ourselves from the inevitable? it feels more logical to just accept that it doesn't matter.",
